Description:
Your Tasks And Responsibilities

The primary responsibilities of this role, Intern, are to:
Work with process Subject Matter Experts (SMEs) on advanced analytics of their process data,utilizing respective tools. Generating data driven models and feeding results into daily work of process scientist;
Help shape the data & analytics platform that is currently being set up.


Who You Are

Your success will be driven by your demonstration of our LIFE values. More specifically related to this position, Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:

Required Qualifications:
Currently enrolled in a minimum of Bachelor program;
Strong verbal and written communication skills;
Ability to deal professionally with internal customers of various organizational levels;
Ability to work effectively within a departmental team and with members of the same or higher organizational levels;
Good organization, documentation, prioritization and scheduling skills together with an overall desire to learn;
Basic problem solving and project management abilities together with a professional image;
Ability to work independently and multi-task;
Data Science and programming skills.
Preferred Qualifications:

Undergraduate focus in Data Science / Data Engineering

